g.text: This Object is used for demand-response load control and other load
control in automation application (not limited to power).
The event identifier as a string.
The duration of the event in minutes.
The criticality of the event. The device receiving the event will
react in an appropriate fashion for the device.
Defines the maximum energy usage of the receiving device, as a
percentage of the device's normal maximum energy usage.
Defines the duty cycle for the load control event, i.e, what
percentage of time the receiving device is allowed to be on.
The application type of the sensor or actuator as a string depending
The timestamp of when the measurement was performed.
Fractional part of the timestamp when sub-second precision is used
